<h2>JavaScript Arrays</h2>

<p>The best way to loop through an array is using a standard for loop:</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
const A = ["Banana", "Orange", "Apple", "Mango"];
let B = A.length;

let C = "<ul>";
for (let i = 0; i < B; i++) {
  C += "<li>" + A[i] + "</li>";
}
C += "</ul>";

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = C;
</script>

</body>
